://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9715951374726032, \"rank\": 0.02040214975904262, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Moroccan women champions are accompanied by a team consisting of coaches Abdelhak Achik and Youssef Sarour, under the supervision of the technical director of the national teams, Othman Fadli.\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 1022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.156131848440601e-16, \"text\": \"Moroccan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}, {\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdelhak_Achik\", \"score\": 0.999999997099394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abdelhak Achik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdelhak_Achik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdelhak_Achik\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During Tokyo 2020 Olympics women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s boxing competitions, Turkey won its first boxing gold medal in the Welterweight category while China won the silver medal, Japan secured its first gold medal in the featherweight category from the Philippines who received the silver medal.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1082, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.6159348461455173, \"rank\": 0.6225473451597326, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 1128, \"end\": 1140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing_at_the_1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999253813468035, \"rank\": 7.462419702737735e-05, \"text\": \"Welterweight\", \"t